abstract: A Stanford University student finds that your online travel -- your clickstream, as it's poetically known -- is not always anonymous. It can often be traced right back to rather precise parts of you.
snippet: A Stanford University student finds that your online travel -- your clickstream, as it's poetically known -- is not always anonymous. It can often be traced right back to rather precise parts of you.
lead_paragraph: The Web is porous. Remarkable information trickles in from everywhere. It also sometimes spills out without its users knowing exactly where or how.

headline.main: Stanford Researcher Finds Lots of Leaky Web Sites
